Used to frequent Shillawon a few times every year before new management and probably won't now.  This is only a comparison (dissapointments) from previous to new as we recently ate there. Here are some of the experiences.  Some of the meats given were actually still frozen. We bbq at home a lot and it's a faux pas to not let the meat come to room temperature before grilling. Not a good first sign.  The ban-chan was generic - nothing special - and you had to ask for the lettuce wrap, garlic and bean paste separately as they do NOT include that in the ban-chan set which was 'odd'. Then if you want a second round, it's $7. 😳  We had two tables together and they swapped out the grill on one side while the other side was COMPLETELY black and smoking. We had to flag down a server to get it switched. Why it wasn't done at the same time showed lack of service which continued.  We asked - and reminded - about napkins, forks (2 children), knives and water. The knives never came. We asked for meats and ban-chan and at least twice.  We had a party of 8 which included 2 children and there was only one other same sized group along with around 4 tables of 2-4 people each - not even close to being crowded as there were CHOKE empty tables. Later on in the night about 7pm, the private room was being used. We came in at 6pm.  There was a customer who actually got out of his chair to flag down the server (who was standing right in front us) to 'remind' her that they still haven't received their side salad.  Then insult to injury, they tack on an automatic 15% gratuity - shouldn't that have been for "service"?? Mind you they've already jacked up the prices from the previous regime.  We've always been told to check out other places but remained loyal till now.  Yes I am Korean and they were shocked when my parents spoke to them in their native tongue but that didn't account for anything as service remained bad.  Overall it was tasteful but not at the price of service, quality and.... well, price.

Delicious food served hot and fast.  The staff is very nice and treat everyone as family.  Lots of street parking and an easy walk from Wal-Mart garage.  Located on the first floor of the residential building near MW Restaurant, 1st Hawaiian bank and Walgreens.  Big tables with a family home atmosphere.  Each table has hot pot or Bar BQ.  Very cool Korean decorations and Korean channel TV playing in the center of the main dining room.  There are a couple big rooms to serve a private party and a Bar.  The only imperfect thing has to be the restrooms.  They are clean, just outdated and cluttered.
